1
00:00:01,361 --> 00:00:07,300
Before a pin bar becomes a pin bar, it will
look like this…very bullish.

2
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:11,691
When you are watching this candle developing
on your charts, you may have an urge to place

3
00:00:11,691 --> 00:00:13,041
a trade.

4
00:00:13,041 --> 00:00:17,591
Your greed tells you to enter, because you’ll
miss a future price move.

5
00:00:17,591 --> 00:00:21,251
And you’re not alone in feeling this urge
to enter.

6
00:00:21,251 --> 00:00:26,731
When reactive traders see candles like this
one, they feel the urge to take a position

7
00:00:26,731 --> 00:00:30,031
in the direction of the candle their seeing.

8
00:00:30,031 --> 00:00:34,171
And when the pin bar is completed, your fear
takes over.

9
00:00:34,171 --> 00:00:39,481
If you entered when this candle looked bullish,
by now you would start to feel a little bit

10
00:00:39,481 --> 00:00:43,901
under pressure in regards to what the market
may do next.

11
00:00:43,901 --> 00:00:47,581
Your trade has gone from being at a profit
to being at a loss.

12
00:00:47,581 --> 00:00:52,891
And if the market goes down any lower, you
will start to consider whether it’s a good

13
00:00:52,891 --> 00:00:55,371
idea staying in the trade.

14
00:00:55,371 --> 00:00:57,771
Again, fear and greed.

15
00:00:57,771 --> 00:01:02,611
I always think like this when I’m considering
a trade.

16
00:01:02,611 --> 00:01:08,560
If you didn’t already know, there are different
types of pin bars which appear in the market.

17
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:14,181
When I say types I don’t mean one pin bar
has a bigger wick than the other, I mean the

18
00:01:14,181 --> 00:01:20,382
causes behind why a pin bar forms in the market
can be different depending on where the pin

19
00:01:20,382 --> 00:01:21,382
bar is found.

20
00:01:21,382 --> 00:01:28,581
There are 2 main causes: when a pin bar appears,
big player took a significant amount of profits

21
00:01:28,581 --> 00:01:34,271
off their existing trades or when they’re
starting to place trades in order to make

22
00:01:34,271 --> 00:01:36,011
the market reverse.

23
00:01:36,011 --> 00:01:41,501
And the best types of Pin Bar setups form
when there has been a sustained moved (either

24
00:01:41,501 --> 00:01:47,331
up or down) and price retraces to an area
of "value" or "interest".

25
00:01:47,331 --> 00:01:52,381
The Strategy explained

26
00:01:52,381 --> 00:01:56,411
At its core, a pin bar is considered a reversal
candlestick.

27
00:01:56,411 --> 00:02:02,551
But, if you try to trade pin bars as reversal
signals when the price is moving in the direction

28
00:02:02,551 --> 00:02:06,831
of the trend, then you are not doing it correctly.

29
00:02:06,831 --> 00:02:13,860
So, to avoid this situation, you’ll use
2 exponential moving averages.

30
00:02:13,860 --> 00:02:20,581
One with a period of 50, and the second one
with a period of 100.

31
00:02:20,581 --> 00:02:24,351
These are very common and followed by many
other traders.

32
00:02:24,351 --> 00:02:30,720
• If the 50 EMA is above the 100 EMA, then
the market is in an uptrend.

33
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:38,711
• If the 50 EMA is below the 100 EMA, then
the market is in a downtrend.

34
00:02:38,711 --> 00:02:45,341
Our strategy involves trading pullbacks, in
the direction of the 2 EMAs, using high volume

35
00:02:45,341 --> 00:02:47,771
pin bars.

36
00:02:47,771 --> 00:02:52,321
When markets trend, they do not just go up
or down in a straight line.

37
00:02:52,321 --> 00:02:57,220
There’s always a period of “rest” before
continuing the trend.

38
00:02:57,220 --> 00:03:02,911
Markets ALWAYS have these pullbacks when trending
and these are great opportunities for you

39
00:03:02,911 --> 00:03:09,031
to get into a trade before the market resumes
its trend.

40
00:03:09,031 --> 00:03:14,891
The area between the 2 EMA is the “sweet
spot” for our entries.

41
00:03:14,891 --> 00:03:21,081
You want to find high volume pin bars, in
the direction of the main trend, rejecting

42
00:03:21,081 --> 00:03:22,831
these levels.

43
00:03:22,831 --> 00:03:28,301
The volume of the pin bar must be higher than
the previous 3 bars.

44
00:03:28,301 --> 00:03:31,981
BEST Signals To Trade

45
00:03:31,981 --> 00:03:35,751
So, what makes a tradable Pin Bar?

46
00:03:35,751 --> 00:03:41,621
I mainly look for several points:
• The "wick" (or tail) should be at least

47
00:03:41,621 --> 00:03:46,271
2 times, ideally 3 times, the length of the
body.

48
00:03:46,271 --> 00:03:54,311
• The body should be present towards either
the upper or lower extreme of the Pin bar.

49
00:03:54,311 --> 00:03:59,021
• The wick should stand out when compared
to surrounding bars.

50
00:03:59,021 --> 00:04:05,181
Generally, Pin Bar signals are only relevant
for the next 4 - 5 bars.

51
00:04:05,181 --> 00:04:11,290
So, if you watch the daily time frame and
a pin bar forms, it will make most of its

52
00:04:11,290 --> 00:04:17,071
impact on future price moves within 4 - 5
days of its creation.

53
00:04:17,071 --> 00:04:23,341
This is because Pin Bars are short duration
setups, and because of this, it makes sense

54
00:04:23,341 --> 00:04:29,911
that they will normally only affect the outcome
of the bars immediately in the future.

55
00:04:29,911 --> 00:04:32,341
Pin Bars should not be traded on their own.

56
00:04:32,341 --> 00:04:38,912
There are many factors that influence whether
or not you should trade a Pin Bar and for

57
00:04:38,912 --> 00:04:44,631
that reason you shouldn’t take a trade solely
based on the fact that a Pin Bar has formed.

58
00:04:44,631 --> 00:04:51,941
This is why we’ll use EMAs for trend direction
and volume to spot interest and active participation

59
00:04:51,941 --> 00:04:53,941
in a future price move.

60
00:04:53,941 --> 00:05:00,111
Also, pin bars that are in heavy traffic or
choppy, range bound markets should not be

61
00:05:00,111 --> 00:05:01,411
traded.

62
00:05:01,411 --> 00:05:07,471
The reason for this is that there is no clear
trend and there are too many areas of interest

63
00:05:07,471 --> 00:05:09,820
for price to stall at.

64
00:05:09,820 --> 00:05:14,581
Finding areas of value

65
00:05:14,581 --> 00:05:21,691
So, pin bars should only be traded when they
form in areas of "value" or "interest".

66
00:05:21,691 --> 00:05:28,261
The more of these areas of interest that converge
together near where the Pin Bar has formed,

67
00:05:28,261 --> 00:05:34,281
the more significant the Pin Bar signal becomes,
this is known as "confluence".

68
00:05:34,281 --> 00:05:39,991
You can use support and resistance levels,
supply and demand areas, but in this video,

69
00:05:39,991 --> 00:05:42,501
we’ll focus on EMAs.

70
00:05:42,501 --> 00:05:48,491
As well as being used to evaluate the trend
direction and strength, EMAs can be used as

71
00:05:48,491 --> 00:05:51,911
dynamic levels of support and resistance.

72
00:05:51,911 --> 00:05:58,391
In some cases, price can be seen to bounce
off certain EMA values almost religiously

73
00:05:58,391 --> 00:06:01,691
during retraces in trending markets.

74
00:06:01,691 --> 00:06:07,871
And when volume confirms the pin bar, you
have several factors which increase the probability

75
00:06:07,871 --> 00:06:11,130
of a successful trade.

76
00:06:11,130 --> 00:06:17,320
The only problem with EMAs is that everybody
uses different period values depending on

77
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:20,551
the time frame and markets they are trading.

78
00:06:20,551 --> 00:06:26,741
My advice is to pick two periods and stick
with them, as once you get some experience

79
00:06:26,741 --> 00:06:32,661
under your belt, you will start to learn how
they behave in different market conditions.

80
00:06:32,661 --> 00:06:39,781
I prefer the h4 and daily time frame, and
I use the 50 and 100 day EMAs, but the choice

81
00:06:39,781 --> 00:06:41,751
is completely up to you.

82
00:06:41,751 --> 00:06:44,570
You can change the parameters as you wish.

83
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:49,630
Just understand the concept and adapt it to
your needs.

84
00:06:49,630 --> 00:06:52,660
We trade Amazon on the hourly time frame.

85
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:59,641
One of the first things you should look for
when you open a chart are the 2 EMAs, to determine

86
00:06:59,641 --> 00:07:04,951
trend direction and find possible areas of
dynamic support or resistance.

87
00:07:04,951 --> 00:07:12,541
In this case, the trend is down, so we look
to short the market.

88
00:07:12,541 --> 00:07:19,181
And this is our pin bar, showing rejection
and indicating a potential trend continuation.

89
00:07:19,181 --> 00:07:24,901
The volume of the pin bar is higher than the
previous 3 candles, so there’s active interest

90
00:07:24,901 --> 00:07:27,171
in the market.

91
00:07:27,171 --> 00:07:34,171
When the low of the pin bar is broken, that’s
our signal to initiate a sell position.

92
00:07:34,171 --> 00:07:36,531
Stop loss above the pin bar.

93
00:07:36,531 --> 00:07:42,471
And in this case, above the 2 EMAs, which
is almost a perfect setup, with another layer

94
00:07:42,471 --> 00:07:44,271
of protection.

95
00:07:44,271 --> 00:07:47,821
Take profit at the next swing low in the price
structure.

96
00:07:47,821 --> 00:07:56,761
A risk to reward ratio of around 2.8.

97
00:07:56,761 --> 00:08:01,971
Perfect trade and we even left profits on
the table.

98
00:08:01,971 --> 00:08:06,581
We move to pound yen on the M30 time frame.

99
00:08:06,581 --> 00:08:13,671
The 50 EMA is above the 100 EMA, so we look
for buy opportunities.

100
00:08:13,671 --> 00:08:18,621
We have our pullback to the EMAs, and here’s
our pin bar.

101
00:08:18,621 --> 00:08:25,421
But look at the volume, is lower than the
previous 4 or 5 bars.

102
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:27,371
So, this is a no trade.

103
00:08:27,371 --> 00:08:31,411
The volume condition isn’t met.

104
00:08:31,411 --> 00:08:34,911
This is unfortunate, because the price indeed
went up.

105
00:08:34,911 --> 00:08:40,541
But in the long run, the volume confirmation
will save your account for many losing trades.

106
00:08:40,541 --> 00:08:42,731
So don’t neglect it.

107
00:08:42,731 --> 00:08:49,361
Let’s move to EURJPY, on my favorite time
frame, the H4.

108
00:08:49,361 --> 00:08:50,851
The same situation.

109
00:08:50,851 --> 00:09:01,071
The trend is up because the 50 EMA is above
the 100 EMA, so we look for long trades.

110
00:09:01,071 --> 00:09:08,421
We have a small pullback to the 50 EMA, and
with this pin bar rejecting the area.

111
00:09:08,421 --> 00:09:14,591
Volume is higher than the previous bars, so
all conditions are met.

112
00:09:14,591 --> 00:09:21,341
When the high of the pin bar is broken, that’s
the signal to initiate a long position.

113
00:09:21,341 --> 00:09:26,281
Stop loss below the low of the pin bar, and
below the 50 EMA.

114
00:09:26,281 --> 00:09:31,421
As for take profit, the distance until the
next swing high doesn’t offer a positive

115
00:09:31,421 --> 00:09:36,761
risk to reward ratio, so we must estimate
our self a potential target.

116
00:09:36,761 --> 00:09:43,001
I’ll set a target of 3, but I’ll monitor
closely the price action at this resistance

117
00:09:43,001 --> 00:09:53,041
area.

118
00:09:53,041 --> 00:09:58,521
In order to be a valid tradeable pattern,
the pin bar must reject the area between the

119
00:09:58,521 --> 00:09:59,901
2 EMAs.

120
00:09:59,901 --> 00:10:02,601
This is a key point in trading pin bars.

121
00:10:02,601 --> 00:10:08,951
In this case, again, we are dealing with a
bullish trend, so we’ll look for a continuation

122
00:10:08,951 --> 00:10:12,251
trade to the upside.

123
00:10:12,251 --> 00:10:16,011
This is the pin bar, rejecting the 50 EMA.

124
00:10:16,011 --> 00:10:22,041
Volume is higher than the previous candles,
so this is a valid setup.

125
00:10:22,041 --> 00:10:27,271
Once we’ve identified the pin bar at the
value area, we wait for the high of candle

126
00:10:27,271 --> 00:10:30,191
to be broken.

127
00:10:30,191 --> 00:10:35,751
Stop loss below the low of the pin bar, and
below the 50 EMA.

128
00:10:35,751 --> 00:10:43,921
We are very close to the most recent high,
so we aim for a risk to reward ratio of 2

129
00:10:43,921 --> 00:10:50,221
or even 3.

130
00:10:50,221 --> 00:10:54,420
Let’s continue.

131
00:10:54,420 --> 00:10:59,321
I see a somewhat deeper pullback to the 100
EMA.

132
00:10:59,321 --> 00:11:02,231
And a pin bar forming right on top of it.

133
00:11:02,231 --> 00:11:08,691
The real body is relatively small, and the
tail of the candle is much longer.

134
00:11:08,691 --> 00:11:14,941
Volume is definitely higher than the previous
bars, we there’s active participation, an

135
00:11:14,941 --> 00:11:18,881
interest in that particular area.

136
00:11:18,881 --> 00:11:23,601
So we’ll enter long at the high of the pin
bar.

137
00:11:23,601 --> 00:11:28,831
We gave a gap up, so the entry price would
be somewhat higher.

138
00:11:28,831 --> 00:11:33,441
Stop loss below the pin bar and below the
100 EMA.

139
00:11:33,441 --> 00:11:39,811
As for targets, I see this major resistance
here, which could stop the price increase,

140
00:11:39,811 --> 00:11:43,621
so let’s take our profit a few points below
this area.

141
00:11:43,621 --> 00:11:47,391
A risk to reward ratio of around 2.5.

142
00:11:47,391 --> 00:11:53,071
Okey, that’s frustrating.

143
00:11:53,071 --> 00:11:58,621
Price almost hit our take profit, but instead
it reversed and stopped us out.

144
00:11:58,621 --> 00:12:01,831
There’s a lesson to be learned here.

145
00:12:01,831 --> 00:12:06,291
What could we have done to manage the trade
better when in profit?

146
00:12:06,291 --> 00:12:14,240
As we entered below the 50 EMA, near the 100
EMA, in the future, when price goes up and

147
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:20,861
consolidates above the 50 EMA, a safer money
management technique is to move the stop loss

148
00:12:20,861 --> 00:12:22,391
to break even.

149
00:12:22,391 --> 00:12:28,251
We don’t allow a profitable trade to become
a losing one.

150
00:12:28,251 --> 00:12:33,921
Some traders will claim that the bigger the
Pin Bar the better, but my experience has

151
00:12:33,921 --> 00:12:39,511
shown that if the Pin Bar is much larger than
the average trading range of the preceding

152
00:12:39,511 --> 00:12:47,391
bars, then it will most likely become a continuation
pattern rather than a reversal pattern.

153
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:53,540
When presented with a massive Pin Bar like
this one on Bitcoin, my advice is to stay

154
00:12:53,540 --> 00:14:54,691
on the sidelines and wait for a better opportunity
to present itself.

155
00:14:54,691 --> 00:14:58,521
If you found value and learned something new,
leave us a like.

156
00:14:58,521 --> 00:15:02,170
This way we’ll know if you'd like to see
more videos like this one.

157
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:06,891
And check out our academy program if you want
to further level up your trading.

158
00:15:06,891 --> 00:15:08,751
Until next time.

